overview: The user tasked the agent with thoroughly testing the sleep
  questionnaire application via the browser. The agent systematically tested the
  application's core functionalities, including the multi-section questionnaire
  flow, dynamic form fields, PDF report generation, and admin login. During
  testing, it confirmed that most features were working as expected, such as
  form validation and API endpoints. It also identified minor issues like ESLint
  warnings and an outdated page title. Following the testing, the agent
  proceeded to implement several improvements and new features, including
  updating the page title, adding new fields for pain and chronic fatigue
  screening, significantly enhancing the report section with detailed sleep
  analysis, updating PDF generation, and implementing a comprehensive CSV export
  for questionnaire data. The agent then committed these changes in logical,
  atomic units following conventional commit best practices.
